pageTitle: Jewelry stolen from two Cambridge Springs homes | NewsLive365
TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {9622=Posted by Andy Alm on Nov 27, 2012 in Andy Alm, Crime, Editors, Headline, Meadville, News, News by City, 8554=CAMBRIDGE SPRINGS – State Police are investigating two jewelry thefts reported recently in the Cambridge Springs area.  Judy Rauenswinter tells police a gold charm bracelet and two gold chains were stolen from her home on Sunnyside Drive.  And Henry Finck says someone took a gold chain and three rings from his home on Thomas Road while it was being remodeled.  Both thefts were believed to have occurred in May.}
